cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.NI

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with network data and proposes a framework to measure nodal characteristics in directed networks. 
2. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The proposed algorithm and estimator can be seen as software engineering tools for sampling and estimation in directed networks. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a novel algorithm for personalized PageRank-based sampling in directed networks. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The proposed framework can be used to measure characteristics of web-based networks such as the World Wide Web. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with network data and proposes a framework for measuring characteristics in directed networks, which is relevant to the networking and internet architecture community.
